<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@engine/macros/page"
      i18n:domain="cc_org">
<head>
  <title metal:fill-slot="title">Public Domain Assertion</title>


  <metal:headers fill-slot="headers">
    <base href="" tal:attributes="href string:${context/@@absolute_url}/zero/" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" 
	  href="http://yui.yahooapis.com/2.4.1/build/button/assets/skins/sam/button.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"
	  href="http://yui.yahooapis.com/2.4.1/build/container/assets/container.css">

<script type="text/javascript"
	src="ext-2.0/adapter/yui/yui-utilities.js"
	tal:attributes="src
	context/++resource++cc/ext-2.0/adapter/yui/yui-utilities.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript"
	src="ext-2.0/adapter/yui/ext-yui-adapter.js"
	tal:attributes="src
	context/++resource++cc/ext-2.0/adapter/yui/ext-yui-adapter.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript"
	src="ext-2.0/ext-all.js"
	tal:attributes="src
	context/++resource++cc/ext-2.0/ext-all.js"></script>

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="zero.css"
	  tal:attributes="href context/++resource++cc/includes/zero.css" />

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="ext-all.css"
	  tal:attributes="href
	  context/++resource++cc/ext-2.0/resources/css/ext-all.css" />

    <script src="zero_chooser.js" type="text/javascript"
       tal:attributes="src context/++resource++cc/includes/zero_chooser.js">
    </script>
  </metal:headers>

</head>

<body>

<metal:left fill-slot="sidebar">
</metal:left>

<metal:title fill-slot="page-header-title"></metal:title>

<metal:body fill-slot="body">
<div class="yui-skin-sam">

  <div id="zero-wizard">

    <div id="page-welcome" class="yui-module">
      <div class="hd">Public Domain Assertion</div>
      <div class="bd">
	<p>
	  The Public Domain Assertion enables you to indicate that a
	  work is free of copyright and any related or neighboring
	  rights such as moral rights, publicity or privacy rights,
	  rights protecting against unfair competition and any rights
	  protecting the extraction, dissemination and reuse of data. 
	</p>

	<p>
	  Using the Public Domain Assertion, you can
	  <strong>Assert</strong> that a work is free of legal
	  encumberances as a matter of fact, for example, because the
	  work <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_Domain#Expiration">is
	  old enough</a> to be in the public domain, or because the
	  work is in a class not protected by copyright such 
	  as <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copyright_status_of_work_by_the_U.S._government">U.S. government
	  works</a>.  Curators and publishers of public domain
	  material may be well placed to make such an assertion. 
	</p>
	<p>
	  <span id="radio2" class="yui-button yui-radio-button">
            <span class="first-child">
              <button type="submit" name="zero-type" value="assertion"
		      id="do-begin">
                continue
              </button>
            </span>
	  </span>

	</p>

      </div>

    </div>

    <div id="page-details" class="x-hide-display">

<metal:assertion define-macro="assertion-ui">

<div id="assertion_ui" class="yui-module">
  <div class="hd">Public Domain Assertion</div>
  <div class="bd">
    <form id="form-details" action="confirm-assertion">
      <input type="hidden" name="license-class" value="zero" />
      <input type="hidden" name="code" value="pd" />

      <div class="form-row">
	<div class="form-question">Your name:</div>
	<div class="form-answer"><input name="name" class="form-field" /></div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-row">
	<div class="form-question">Your URL:</div>
	<div class="form-answer"><input name="actor_href"
					class="form-field"/>
	</div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-row">
	<div class="form-question">Title of the work:</div>
	<div class="form-answer"><input name="work_title" class="form-field"/></div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-row">
	<div class="form-question">URL of the work:</div>
	<div class="form-answer"><input name="work_url" class="form-field"/></div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-row">
	<div class="form-question">
	  <p>I assert that this work is free of any copyrights because:
	  </p>
	</div>
	<div class="form-answer">
	  <input name="assertion_reason" type="checkbox" class="reason"
		 value="us_govt" />
	  <label>the work was created by the U.S. Government.</label> <br/>

	  <input name="assertion_reason" type="checkbox" class="reason" 
		 value="us_1923" />
	  <label for="us_1923">the work was created in the U.S. before 1923.</label> <br/>

	  <input name="assertion_reason" type="checkbox" class="reason" 
		 value="other" id="enable_other_assertion_reason"/>
	  <label for="other">other:</label> <br/>
          <input name="other_assertion_reason" id="other_assertion_reason"
                 class="form-field" />
	</div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-row">
	<div class="form-question">&nbsp;</div>
	<div class="form-answer">
	  <input type="submit" id="details-submit" name="field1" 
		 value="continue"> 
	</div>
      </div>

    </form>
    <br clear="both"/>&nbsp;
  </div>

</metal:assertion>

    </div>

    <div id="page-confirmation" class="x-hide-display">

<metal:confirm-assertion define-macro="confirm-assertion">
      <div id="confirm-assertion" class="yui-module">
	<div class="hd">Confirm Public Domain Assertion</div>
	<div class="bd">

	    <p>Asserting that a work is free of rights lets others
	    know that they may reuse it without restriction.  Are you
	    certain you wish to do this?
	    </p>

	    <div class="form-row yui-buttongroup">

	      <span class="yui-button">
		<span class="first-child">
		  <button type="submit" id="decline-submit"
			  name="decline">
		    No, I Do Not Assert
		  </button>
		</span>
	      </span>

	      <span class="yui-button">
		<span class="first-child">
		  <button type="submit" id="confirm-submit" 
			  name="confirm">
		    I So Assert
		  </button>
		</span>
	      </span>

	    </div>

	</div>
      </div>
</metal:confirm-assertion>

    </div>

    <div id="page-results" class="x-hide-display">

  <div id="results" class="yui-module">
    <div class="hd">Public Domain Assertion Results</div>
    <div class="bd" id="dedication-results">

      <p>Choose which style of button you'd like on your webpage:</p>

      <div class="licensebox" align="center">
	<table>
	  <tr>
	    <td valign="bottom" align="center">
	      <img src="http://labs.creativecommons.org/zero/images/88x31/cc-zero.png"
	      style="border:0px;" /><br/>
	      <input type="radio" name="button" checked
             onclick="swapbutton('http://labs.creativecommons.org/zero/images/88x31/cc-zero.png')"
	      />
	    </td>
	    <td valign="bottom" align="center">
	      <img src="http://labs.creativecommons.org/zero/images/80x15/cc-zero.png"
	      style="border:0px;" /><br/>
	      <input type="radio" name="button"
             onclick="swapbutton('http://labs.creativecommons.org/zero/images/80x15/cc-zero.png')"
	      />
	    </td>

	  </tr>
	</table>
      </div>

      <span i18n:translate="">
	Here's a preview of how your assertion will appear on your
	site:
      </span>

      <div class="preview" id="results-preview">
      </div>

      <div class="hd" style="margin-top:10px;">What to do next</div>
      <h3>Have a website?</h3>
      <p>Copy the text below to your Web site to let your visitors
      know what license applies to your works.</p> 
      <textarea id="results-html" cols="70" rows="6" onfocus="select()">
      </textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="ft"></div>
  </div>

  <div id="page-bailout" class="x-hide-display">

    <metal:bailout define-macro="post-bailout">
      <div id="bailout" class="yui-module">
	<div class="hd">Public Domain Assertion: Declined</div>
	<div class="bd">
	  <p>What would you like to do next?</p>
	  <ul>
	    <li><a href="./index.html">start over</a></li>
	    <li><a href="http://wiki.creativecommons.org/CcZero">learn more</a></li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
      </div>
    </metal:bailout>

  </div>


    </div>

  </div>
  

</div>
</metal:body>

</body>
</html>
